Compute Pairwise Similarity or Distance Metrics Between Signatures

Source: R/statistics.R
sig_collection_pairwise_stats.Rd

Calculates a specified pairwise metric for all unique pairs of signatures in a sigverse collection. Supported metrics are:

  • cosine_similarity: returns values in [0, 1], where 1 indicates identical signatures

  • L2: Euclidean distance between signatures

  • L1: Manhattan distance between signatures

Usage

sig_collection_pairwise_stats(
  signatures,
  metric = c("cosine_similarity", "L2", "L1"),
  format = c("data.frame", "matrix")
)

Arguments

signatures

A signature collection, either as a named list of sigverse signature data.frames or as a numeric matrix of fractional values (contexts × signatures). Column names are used as signature IDs.

metric

Character; one of c("cosine_similarity", "L2", "L1"). Determines which pairwise metric to compute.

format

Character; one of c("data.frame", "matrix").

  • "data.frame" (default): returns a long-format data.frame with columns S1, S2, and <metric>.

  • "matrix": returns an N×N symmetric numeric matrix of pairwise metrics (dimnames = signature IDs). The diagonal is set to 1 for cosine similarity, and 0 for the distance metrics.

Value

Depending on format:

data.frame

A data.frame with one row per unique signature pair, and columns S1, S2, and the chosen metric (named after metric).

matrix

A symmetric numeric matrix of pairwise metrics, with row and column names corresponding to signature IDs.

Details

The input may be supplied either as:

  • A named list of sigverse signature data.frames (each validated via sigshared::assert_signature_collection()), or

  • A numeric matrix (rows = mutation contexts, columns = signatures) with non-NULL, unique column names.

Before computing any metric, each column is normalized to sum to 1 (via sigshared::compute_fraction()), ensuring minor rounding errors in provided fractions do not affect results.
